main event: A person in Wausau, Wisconsin observed a stationary, blueish-green, basketball-sized object with flashing lights in the sky for about 5 minutes on March 30, 1966.
interesting points: The object was stationary and did not move during the 5-minute observation period.
Air Force personnel in the area at the same time also observed a slow-moving aircraft that they assumed was flying from Madison to Wausau.
The same group of Air Force personnel also reported seeing a bright, slightly green star high in the northeast.
The observer was a city patrolman, and his reliability was estimated to be good.
The weather was very clear with surface winds of 19 knots, and there was no other unusual activity or conditions that could have explained the sighting.
